Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
load_failure_report(25.10)                          load_failure_report(25.10)

Name
       load_failure_report  -  Loads the failure report generated while debug-
       ging timing results

Syntax
        load_failure_report

       [-help]

       -file <filename>

       Loads the failure report generated while debugging timing results. This
       failure report contains various reasons that limit timing debug closure
       during automated ECO. This command generates the Failure  Catalog  File
       (FCF) in the format used by the Failure Catalog Browser (FCB).

       Prior  to the introduction of this command, this functionality was per-
       formed only through the signoffOptDesign command.

       For more information, see the Debugging Timing Results chapter  of  the
       Innovus User Guide document.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each load_failure_report parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man load_failure_report

       -file <filename>
              Specifies  the name of the file describing the failure category.
              This is a mandatory parameter.

Related Information
              * signoffOptDesign

              * The Debugging Timing Results chapter of the Innovus User Guide
                document.

